        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 10:00PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 1000 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Burnwell, or 14 miles east of Madison, moving southeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Burnwell, Powellton, Whitesville, Sylvester, Dorothy, Leewood,
Stickney, Artie, Naoma, Prenter, and Eskdale.

This includes West Virginia Turnpike between mile markers 60 and 68.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
